{"type":"message","id":"a5873020","parentId":"377d791d","timestamp":"2026-05-22T04:21:14.263Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that the pipeline went through:\n1. IncrementalBuild pipeline build succeed (at log line 664179)\n2. Upload CDN (begin at 11:52:15, end at 11:52:17, 2.29s)\n\nBut the owner says \"打资源包这一步好像没运行一样\". This could mean:\n1. The incremental build is too fast (just 3 samples of BuildAssetBundles, 8.7 seconds total), so it looks like nothing happened\n2. Or maybe the bundles didn't actually get rebuilt with new content\n\nThe logs show \"IncrementalBuild pipeline build succeed\" which means the incremental/delta build IS running. But in incremental mode, if files haven't changed, it might be very fast and seem like nothing happened.\n\nWait, but we DID have 2 files changed in git pull (VirtualKeyboardController.cs and UISoloChatPage_Base.Input.cs). Those are .cs files, not asset bundles. They would trigger script recompilation but not necessarily bundle rebuilding unless they reference specific assets.\n\nLet me look at the bundle sizes more carefully. The logs show:\n- First build: \"Built-in AssetBundleManifest\" at 0.1 kb\n- Second: 12.1 kb \n- Third: 204.6 kb\n\nThese are from different runs. The last run (today's) had 204.6 kb.\n\nActually, looking at it more carefully, the output from the sub-agent said:\n```\n**打资源包（AssetBundle）** - 已完成（含 Bundle 加密）\n```\n\nBut from the logs, `BuildAssetBundles` only took 8.7s total (3 samples), which is very fast. This might be normal for incremental builds if there are few changes, but the owner seems to think it's too fast/skipped.\n\nLet me look at more details to understand what's happening. Maybe I should look for the actual bundle output directory to see if files were updated.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_D0OucXaJ6NBCIcvH8nf57689","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"powershell \"Select-String -Path 'E:\\Solo\\